rComments: This is a mandatory course for a lot inspiring health care professionals-nurses, SLPs; and I found the course needlessly difficult (however it is interesting). The tests require a lot of regurgitation of lecture material. To get a good mark one must hang on to her every words. She didn't respond to my 2 emails. The second midterm is ridiculous.

Her lectures were good but I would seriously avoid the PSY210 class or any of her classes in general. She took FOREVER to give us our marks back for the exam, way after summer school started. The second midterm was BRUTAL, the average was so low. Would avoid at all costs.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']
